From e71fe9064103c49ae3c26062f0121fe3fee6468a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter Jung <admin@ptr1337.dev>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 18:57:35 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 23/44] drm/i915/psr: Accept PSR2 Early Transport panels
 without explicit Y-coord bit

PSR Early Transport (version 04h, DP_PSR2_WITH_Y_COORD_ET_SUPPORTED)
implies Y-coordinate support by definition. The su_support check was
requiring the Y-coordinate requirement bit explicitly, which incorrectly
excluded ET panels from selective update support.

Relax the condition to also accept ET panels regardless of the
Y-coordinate requirement bit, allowing selective updates to work on
these panels.

Signed-off-by: Peter Jung <admin@ptr1337.dev>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
index 598fe769a..6d0074564 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
@@ -710,8 +710,14 @@ static void _psr_init_dpcd(struct intel_dp *intel_dp, struct intel_connector *co
 		 * To support PSR version 02h and PSR version 03h without
 		 * Y-coordinate requirement panels we would need to enable
 		 * GTC first.
+		 *
+		 * Early Transport (version 04h) implies Y-coordinate
+		 * support. Accept it without explicit Y-coordinate
+		 * requirement bit.
 		 */
-		connector->dp.psr_caps.su_support = y_req &&
+		connector->dp.psr_caps.su_support =
+			(y_req || connector->dp.psr_caps.dpcd[0] ==
+			 DP_PSR2_WITH_Y_COORD_ET_SUPPORTED) &&
 			intel_alpm_aux_wake_supported(intel_dp);
 		drm_dbg_kms(display->drm, "PSR2 %ssupported\n",
 			    connector->dp.psr_caps.su_support ? "" : "not ");
